parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spongy Brake Pedal and Squealing Noise
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A spongy brake pedal can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents. The squealing noise may indicate worn-out brake pads, which can further compromise braking performance.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes squeal loudly when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unbalanced Brake Performance and ABS Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unbalanced brake performance can cause the vehicle to stop short or lose control, leading to accidents. The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can further exacerbate the situation.
symptoms: the front ABS brakes lock up
the rear wheels do not lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Uneven Brake Wear and Premature Wear of Front Disc Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven brake wear can lead to reduced braking performance, vibrations, and noise. Premature wear of front disc brakes can increase the risk of brake failure and accidents.
symptoms: The driver's side brakes continue to wear
the front disc brakes wear prematurely.
